\begin_layout Standard
Flakes of thin crystal were manufactured into Hall bar and four-point probe
 FET devices for electronic characterization, both on conductive substrates
 of doped silicon with an insulating layer of 300nm thermally grown 
\begin_inset Formula $\textrm{Si:P/Si}\textrm{O}_{2}$
\end_inset

.
 Source-drain current 
\begin_inset Formula $I_{D}$
\end_inset

 was measured against voltage bias 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{DS}$
\end_inset

 from 0 to 5 V, and separately for 0 to -5 V, for fixed back gate voltages.
 Gate voltages were fixed in 25 V intervals from -75 V to 75 V for each
 sequence.
 Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:In2Se3-SampleA-I_DSvV_DS"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 shows the data for sample A.
 The rapid change in 
\begin_inset Formula $I_{D}$
\end_inset

 around 0 V is indicative of two back-to-back Schottky diodes, see section
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:Metal-Semiconductor-Metal-conduc"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 Samples B and C showed a similar measurement with both the increasing and
 decreasing 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{DS}$
\end_inset

 bias for fixed gate voltages, figures 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Sample-B-IDvsVDS"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Sample-C-IDvsVDS"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 None of the samples measured were seen to saturate within 
\begin_inset Formula $\pm10$
\end_inset

 V for any gate bias.
 The lower 
\begin_inset Formula $I_{D}$
\end_inset

 for negative 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{DS}$
\end_inset

 bias than positive is typical of n-type semiconductors, which is seen in
 most reports of 
\begin_inset Formula $\textrm{\ensuremath{\alpha}-In}_{2}\textrm{Se}_{3}$
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "island2015gatecontrolled,1986electrical"
literal "true"

\end_inset

.
 Sample A 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{DS}$
\end_inset

 bias was cycled from 0 V, 10 V, -10V, to 0 V, forming asymmetric hysteresis
 in the current.
 The switching behavior is similar to previous reports of 
\begin_inset Formula $\textrm{\ensuremath{\alpha}-In}_{2}\textrm{Se}_{3}$
\end_inset

 transistors, where the ferroelectric polarization field is thought to modify
 the Schottky barrier between the material and the metal leads.<FIXME Refs>
